You are building the FRONTEND for a hackathon project called **IdentiX**.

Project:
- Decentralized Identity (DID) & Verifiable Credentials (VC) platform
- Hackathon MVP (18-hour scope)
- Focus: clean UI, clear flows, demo readiness
- NOT production-grade, NOT enterprise auth

====================================================
TECH STACK (MANDATORY)
====================================================
- Framework: React (Vite or Next.js – choose one)
- Language: JavaScript (NOT TypeScript)
- Styling: TailwindCSS
- HTTP Client: axios / fetch
- QR Code:
  - Generation: qrcode.react
  - Scanning: react-qr-reader
- Wallet:
  - MetaMask ONLY for Issuer & Verifier
  - User wallet is app-managed (seed phrase based)

====================================================
ARCHITECTURE RULES (VERY IMPORTANT)
====================================================
1. Frontend NEVER:
   - Talks to blockchain directly
   - Verifies cryptographic signatures
   - Stores issuer private keys

2. Frontend ONLY:
   - Calls backend REST APIs
   - Displays verification results
   - Generates and scans QR codes
   - Manages basic UI state

3. Backend endpoints already exist:
   - /api/did/*
   - /api/credentials/*
   - /api/blockchain/*

DO NOT invent new APIs.

====================================================
GENERATE 3 SEPARATE FRONTEND APPS
====================================================

Create a `frontend/` folder with:

frontend/
 ├── wallet/     → USER (Holder)
 ├── verifier/   → VERIFIER
 └── issuer/     → ISSUER

Each app must be independent and runnable.

====================================================
1️⃣ USER WALLET UI (frontend/wallet)
====================================================

Purpose:
- User owns credentials
- Stores and shares credentials
- No blockchain interaction

Pages to generate:

1. Welcome Page
- Buttons:
  - "Create New Wallet"
  - "Recover Wallet"

2. Create Wallet Page
- Auto-call POST /api/did/create
- Display 12-word seed phrase
- Checkbox: "I have saved my seed phrase"
- Show generated DID
- Continue to wallet

3. Recover Wallet Page
- Input seed phrase
- Call POST /api/did/recover
- Restore DID

4. Credentials List Page
- Fetch credentials from backend
- Card layout:
  - Credential type
  - Issuer name
  - Issue date

5. Credential Detail Page
- Full credential display
- Button: "Share via QR"
- Generate QR containing credential JSON or credential ID

DO NOT:
- Add selective disclosure
- Add blockchain data
- Add login/auth

====================================================
2️⃣ VERIFIER UI (frontend/verifier)
====================================================

Purpose:
- Verify credentials
- See clear verification result

Pages to generate:

1. Landing Page
- Button: "Verify Credential"

2. QR Scan Page
- Camera QR scan
- Manual paste credential JSON / ID
- On scan → call GET /api/credentials/verify

3. Verification Result Page
Show ONLY:
- Status:
  ✅ VERIFIED
  ❌ INVALID
  ⚠️ REVOKED
- Issuer name
- Issue date
- Credential type

DO NOT:
- Store verification history
- Ask for user identity
- Show wallet or blockchain internals

====================================================
3️⃣ ISSUER UI (frontend/issuer)
====================================================

Purpose:
- Issue and revoke credentials
- Trusted entity (university / employer)

Pages to generate:

1. Issuer Login Page
- MetaMask connect
- Show connected wallet address
- Backend will validate trust

2. Issue Credential Page
Form fields:
- Holder DID
- Credential type
- Credential title
- Issue date

On submit:
- Call POST /api/credentials/issue
- Show success message

3. Issued Credentials Page
- List credentials issued
- Status: Active / Revoked

4. Revoke Credential Page
- Input credential ID
- Button: "Revoke"
- Call POST /api/credentials/revoke

====================================================
COMMON REQUIREMENTS FOR ALL UIs
====================================================
- Clean TailwindCSS styling
- Simple layout
- Clear buttons and labels
- Loading states
- Error messages from backend
- Mobile responsive (basic)

====================================================
OUTPUT EXPECTATION
====================================================
Generate:
- Folder structure
- React components
- API integration
- Minimal Tailwind styling
- README in each app explaining how to run

IMPORTANT:
- Keep it SIMPLE
- Prioritize DEMO FLOW:
  Issue → Receive → Share QR → Verify → Revoke

Start by generating the frontend folder structure and wallet app first, then verifier, then issuer.
